Semi-Pro (2008)

Three men, three dreams. It&#039;s 1976 in Flint, Michigan. Jackie Moon&#039;s 
American Basketball Association team languishes in last place, with 
few fans in the seats. Jackie dreams of a merger with the NBA. A 
tough-minded point guard named Monix is at the end of his career; 
he&#039;s played on the champion Celtics but accepts a trade to Flint to 
be close to Lynn, the love of his life. Clarence "Coffee" Brown dreams 
of stardom: he&#039;s the Tropics&#039; best player, but he&#039;s a hotdog who doesn&#039;t 
value teamwork. When the trio learns that a merger is in the works that 
won&#039;t include the Tropics, they pull the team together to try to achieve 
the impossible. Can dreams come true in Flint?
